Jacques Suzanne (1880-1967), French-born American explorer and dog breeder.  
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacques_Suzanne" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacques_Suzanne</a>

In May 1914 he made the papers by leading his team--two 15-foot sleds, twenty dogs, and three men--down Fifth Avenue, &quot;on their way to the polar regions.&quot;
